{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PsutXn2cfEDcTG8s8Z6gfm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 5.1: Code Review Observability Check\n     2→\n     3→Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a reviewer,\n    10→I want static analysis results included in code review,\n    11→so that missing log statements are caught before verification.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. **Given** `patches/review/enforcement.md` exists, **When** read after this story is implemented, **Then** it includes a section titled \"### Observability\" that instructs the review agent: \"Run `semgrep scan --config patches/observability/` and report gaps.\" <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→2. **Given** static analysis finds 3 missing log statements, **When** code review processes the results, **Then** each gap is listed as a review issue with file path, line number, and description (e.g., \"src/lib/docker.ts:42 — catch block without logging\"). <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    17→3. **Given** no observability gaps are found by static analysis, **When** code review completes the observability check, **Then** the observability section passes silently — no false-positive warnings emitted. <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    18→4. **Given** Semgrep is not installed on the review machine, **When** code review runs the observability check, **Then** it reports \"static analysis skipped — install semgrep\" as a warning and does NOT fail the review. <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    19→5. **Given** `patches/dev/enforcement.md` exists, **When** read after this story is implemented, **Then** it includes an instruction: \"Run `semgrep scan --config patches/observability/` before committing and fix any gaps.\" <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→6. **Given** the observability Semgrep rules in `patches/observability/*.yaml`, **When** `semgrep scan --config patches/observability/ --json <projectDir>` is run on a project with known observability gaps, **Then** the JSON output contains entries with `check_id`, `path`, `start.line`, and `extra.message` fields. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→\n    22→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    23→\n    24→- [x] Task 1: Update `patches/review/enforcement.md` with observability section (AC: #1, #3, #4)\n    25→  - [x] 1.1: Add `### Observability` section after existing \"### Proof Quality Checks\" section\n    26→  - [x] 1.2: Include instruction to run `semgrep scan --config patches/observability/` against changed files\n    27→  - [x] 1.3: Include instruction to list each gap as a review issue (file, line, description)\n    28→  - [x] 1.4: Include instruction that if Semgrep is not installed, log a warning and continue — do not fail review\n    29→  - [x] 1.5: Include instruction that zero gaps means the check passes silently\n    30→\n    31→- [x] Task 2: Update `patches/dev/enforcement.md` with pre-commit observability instruction (AC: #5)\n    32→  - [x] 2.1: In the existing \"### Observability\" section, add instruction to run Semgrep before committing\n    33→  - [x] 2.2: Reference `patches/observability/` as the rule config directory\n    34→\n    35→- [x] Task 3: Write unit tests verifying patch content (AC: #1, #5)\n    36→  - [x] 3.1: Create `src/modules/review/__tests__/observability-patch.test.ts`\n    37→  - [x] 3.2: Test that `patches/review/enforcement.md` contains \"### Observability\" section\n    38→  - [x] 3.3: Test that `patches/review/enforcement.md` contains `semgrep scan --config patches/observability/` instruction\n    39→  - [x] 3.4: Test that `patches/review/enforcement.md` contains skip/warning guidance for missing Semgrep\n    40→  - [x] 3.5: Test that `patches/dev/enforcement.md` contains `semgrep scan --config patches/observability/` instruction\n    41→  - [x] 3.6: Target 100% coverage on new test file\n    42→\n    43→- [x] Task 4: Verify Semgrep rule output format (AC: #6)\n    44→  - [x] 4.1: Ensure existing `patches/observability/*.yaml` rules are valid Semgrep YAML (already done in Epic 1 — regression check only)\n    45→  - [x] 4.2: Add a test that parses mock Semgrep JSON output and confirms `check_id`, `path`, `start.line`, and `extra.message` fields are present\n    46→\n    47→- [x] Task 5: Integration verification (AC: all)\n    48→  - [x] 5.1: `npm run build` — verify tsup compiles without errors\n    49→  - [x] 5.2: `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, no regressions\n    50→  - [x] 5.3: Verify no file exceeds 300 lines (NFR9)\n    51→  - [x] 5.4: Verify review patch reads correctly as markdown\n    52→\n    53→## Dev Notes\n    54→\n    55→### Architecture References\n    56→\n    57→This story implements FR26 (code review includes static analysis results) and FR28 (patches updated with observability enforcement). It builds on:\n    58→- Epic 1 (Stories 1.1–1.3): Semgrep rules in `patches/observability/`, the `analyze()` function in `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts`\n    59→- Epic 2 (Story 2.2): Observability hook enforcement pattern\n    60→- Architecture Decision 1: Semgrep as configurable static analyzer\n    61→- Architecture Decision 6: Module structure with `patches/review/` for review enforcement\n    62→\n    63→### Key Implementation Details\n    64→\n    65→**This story is primarily a patch update, not a code change.** The review agent reads `patches/review/enforcement.md` at review time and follows its instructions. The dev agent reads `patches/dev/enforcement.md` during development. Both patches already exist — this story adds observability sections to them.\n    66→\n    67→**No new TypeScript modules needed.** The `analyze()` function from `src/modules/observability/index.ts` already exists and runs Semgrep. The review agent calls Semgrep directly via the CLI as instructed by the patch. The analyzer module is used by `codeharness audit`, not by the review patch.\n    68→\n    69→**Semgrep CLI, not programmatic API.** The patch tells the review agent to run `semgrep scan --config patches/observability/ --json`. The agent processes the JSON output and reports gaps. This is intentional — the review agent is an LLM reading a patch, not code invoking a function.\n    70→\n    71→**Graceful degradation.** If Semgrep is not installed, the review agent should warn and continue. This matches the existing pattern in `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts` where `analyze()` returns a warning result when Semgrep is missing.\n    72→\n    73→**Gap report format.** Semgrep JSON output includes `results[]` where each entry has `check_id` (rule ID), `path` (file), `start.line` (line number), and `extra.message` (description). The review agent should extract these and list them as review issues.\n    74→\n    75→### Existing Code to Reuse\n    76→\n    77→- `patches/review/enforcement.md` — existing review enforcement patch to extend\n    78→- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` — existing dev enforcement patch to extend\n    79→- `patches/observability/*.yaml` — Semgrep rules already shipped (catch-without-logging, function-no-debug-log, error-path-no-log)\n    80→- `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts` — reference for Semgrep invocation pattern and graceful degradation\n    81→- `src/modules/observability/types.ts` — `AnalyzerResult`, `ObservabilityGap` types for understanding gap shape\n    82→\n    83→### What This Story Does NOT Include\n    84→\n    85→- No new TypeScript modules or CLI commands — this is a patch-only change\n    86→- No programmatic integration of `analyze()` into the review orchestrator — the review agent runs Semgrep directly via CLI\n    87→- No runtime observability (that's Story 5.2)\n    88→- No changes to `src/modules/review/orchestrator.ts` — the orchestrator invokes the BMAD code-review workflow which reads the patch\n    89→- No Semgrep installation automation — users must install Semgrep separately\n    90→\n    91→### Dependencies\n    92→\n    93→- **Depends on:** Epic 1 (Semgrep rules exist in `patches/observability/`) — DONE\n    94→- **Depended on by:** None directly. Story 5.2 covers verification runtime integration separately.\n    95→\n    96→### File Size Constraint\n    97→\n    98→Each new file must be under 300 lines per NFR9.\n    99→- `patches/review/enforcement.md` — modification only, adding ~15-20 lines\n   100→- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` — modification only, adding ~3-5 lines\n   101→- `src/modules/review/__tests__/observability-patch.test.ts` — ~50-80 lines (patch content tests)\n   102→\n   103→### Previous Story Intelligence (Story 4.2 Dockerfile Template & Dev Integration)\n   104→\n   105→- Dev enforcement patch was updated in Story 4.2 with Dockerfile maintenance guidance — same pattern applies here\n   106→- Patch updates are simple markdown additions — no build or compile step needed\n   107→- Tests validate patch content by reading the file and checking for required strings\n   108→- The `patches/` directory is a first-class artifact — changes there are as important as code changes\n   109→\n   110→### Git Intelligence\n   111→\n   112→Recent commits show Epic 4 complete. Patterns:\n   113→- Patch files in `patches/` are markdown, updated by appending sections\n   114→- Tests for patch content use `readFileSync` and string matching\n   115→- Result<T> pattern with `ok()` and `fail()` from `src/types/result.ts`\n   116→- Barrel exports from `index.ts` for module boundaries\n   117→- 100% test coverage on new code\n   118→\n   119→### References\n   120→\n   121→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 1] — Semgrep as static analyzer\n   122→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 6] — Module structure, patches/review/\n   123→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 5.1] — Acceptance criteria\n   124→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-operational-excellence.md#FR26] — Code review includes static analysis\n   125→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-operational-excellence.md#FR28] — Patches updated with observability enforcement\n   126→- [Source: patches/review/enforcement.md] — Existing review enforcement patch\n   127→- [Source: patches/dev/enforcement.md] — Existing dev enforcement patch\n   128→- [Source: src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts] — Semgrep invocation pattern\n   129→\n   130→### Project Structure Notes\n   131→\n   132→- Modified files: `patches/review/enforcement.md` (add Observability section), `patches/dev/enforcement.md` (add Semgrep pre-commit instruction)\n   133→- New files: `src/modules/review/__tests__/observability-patch.test.ts` (patch content validation tests)\n   134→- No module boundary changes — patches are independent artifacts read by agents at runtime\n   135→\n   136→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   137→## Verification Requirements\n   138→\n   139→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/5-1-code-review-observability-check.proof.md`)\n   140→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   141→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100% of all new code in src/)\n   142→\n   143→## Documentation Requirements\n   144→\n   145→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (src/modules/review/AGENTS.md if tests added there)\n   146→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/5-1-code-review-observability-check.md`\n   147→\n   148→## Testing Requirements\n   149→\n   150→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   151→- [ ] All I/O mocked (filesystem reads for patch content)\n   152→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   153→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   154→\n   155→## Dev Agent Record\n   156→\n   157→### Agent Model Used\n   158→\n   159→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   160→\n   161→### Debug Log References\n   162→\n   163→### Completion Notes List\n   164→\n   165→- Added `### Observability` section to `patches/review/enforcement.md` with Semgrep scan instruction, gap reporting format, silent-pass on zero gaps, and graceful skip when Semgrep is not installed\n   166→- Added pre-commit Semgrep scan instruction to existing `### Observability` section in `patches/dev/enforcement.md`\n   167→- Created `src/modules/review/__tests__/observability-patch.test.ts` with 8 tests: 5 for review patch content, 2 for dev patch content, 1 for Semgrep JSON output format contract\n   168→- Build passes, all 2853 tests pass across 111 test files, no regressions\n   169→- All files under 300 lines (NFR9 compliant)\n   170→\n   171→### File List\n   172→\n   173→- `patches/review/enforcement.md` (modified) — added Observability section with Semgrep integration instructions\n   174→- `patches/dev/enforcement.md` (modified) — added pre-commit Semgrep scan instruction\n   175→- `src/modules/review/__tests__/observability-patch.test.ts` (new) — patch content validation tests and Semgrep JSON format contract test\n   176→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RNa1Ceka4JYVbubAdWpc5X","session_id":"63766b2b-ee05-46af-a819-a3f0370845d2","uuid":"37e87629-8057-468f-8760-9a9b2ce7d8fc","timestamp":"2026-03-21T06:29:23.618Z"}
