{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KDNwgQSZA5ozK6DTegXT7n","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→stepsCompleted: [1, 2]\n     3→lastStep: 2\n     4→status: complete\n     5→completedAt: '2026-03-17'\n     6→inputDocuments:\n     7→  - prd-overhaul.md\n     8→  - product-brief-codeharness-arch-overhaul-2026-03-17.md\n     9→  - ux-design-specification.md (v1, reworked)\n    10→workflowType: 'ux-design'\n    11→note: 'Full CLI UX spec — reworked for architecture overhaul with status visibility, failure detail, live mode'\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→# CLI UX Specification — codeharness (v2)\n    15→\n    16→**Date:** 2026-03-17\n    17→**Revision:** Architecture overhaul — reworked for visibility, responsiveness, and clear failure reporting\n    18→\n    19→## Overview\n    20→\n    21→codeharness is a CLI tool. No GUI, no web interface, no visual design. The UX is the developer experience in the terminal: command output, error messages, progress reporting, hook feedback, and proof document structure.\n    22→\n    23→**Core UX principle:** One screen, full picture. Progressive detail. Failures are specific and actionable.\n    24→\n    25→**Target user:** Developer who runs codeharness and checks back later. Needs to understand what happened in 10 seconds, drill into failures in 2 minutes, and never spelunk through log files.\n    26→\n    27→## Command Surface\n    28→\n    29→```\n    30→codeharness <command> [options]\n    31→\n    32→Commands:\n    33→  init        Initialize harness in current project\n    34→  run         Start autonomous execution loop\n    35→  verify      Run verification pipeline for a story\n    36→  status      Show project state, run progress, and action items\n    37→  bridge      Import BMAD stories into beads\n    38→  onboard     Scan existing project and generate onboarding plan\n    39→  teardown    Remove harness artifacts (preserves project code)\n    40→  state       Read/write harness state flags\n    41→  retry       Manage story retry state\n    42→\n    43→Options:\n    44→  --json      Machine-readable JSON output (all commands)\n    45→  --verbose   Verbose output for debugging\n    46→  --help      Show help\n    47→  --version   Show version\n    48→```\n    49→\n    50→### Command-Specific Options"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RNa1Ceka4JYVbubAdWpc5X","session_id":"63766b2b-ee05-46af-a819-a3f0370845d2","uuid":"00a1154a-397d-47f1-aa29-9613acd919c1","timestamp":"2026-03-21T06:30:01.859Z"}
