{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013fmuS6Bjo7u5BEy6AYYC3w","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 5.2: Verification Runtime Integration\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a verifier,\n    10→I want observability gaps automatically detected during verification,\n    11→so that proof documents include observability evidence alongside functional results.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. **Given** `patches/verify/story-verification.md` exists, **When** read after this story is implemented, **Then** it includes a section titled \"### Observability Evidence\" that instructs the verifier: \"After each `docker exec` command, query the observability backend for log events from the last 30 seconds. If zero events, include `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` in the AC section.\" <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→2. **Given** `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` already contains a \"Step 3.5: Observability Check After Each Command\" section, **When** the `verifyPromptTemplate()` function is called, **Then** the generated prompt includes the observability check instructions with the correct VictoriaLogs query URL and the `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tagging instruction. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. **Given** a proof document with 8 AC sections and 2 containing `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags, **When** `parseObservabilityGaps(proofContent)` is called, **Then** it returns `{ totalACs: 8, gapCount: 2, coveredCount: 6 }` and runtime observability coverage is reported as 75%. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→4. **Given** a proof document with observability gaps, **When** `verifyStory(key)` completes, **Then** `VerifyResult.observabilityGapCount` reflects the gap count and `VerifyResult.runtimeCoveragePercent` reflects the coverage — reported alongside functional pass/fail results. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→5. **Given** verification completes with runtime observability data, **When** `saveRuntimeCoverage()` is called, **Then** `sprint-state.json` is updated under `observability.runtime` with `coveragePercent` and `lastValidationTimestamp` — separate from static coverage under `observability.static`. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→6. **Given** the observability stack is not running during verification, **When** the verifier queries the backend, **Then** it reports \"observability check skipped — backend not reachable\" as a warning and does NOT fail the verification. <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    21→7. **Given** `patches/verify/story-verification.md` is read by the verification workflow, **When** the verifier follows its instructions, **Then** the proof document includes both functional evidence (`docker exec` output) and observability evidence (log query results or `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags) for each AC. <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    22→\n    23→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    24→\n    25→- [x] Task 1: Update `patches/verify/story-verification.md` with observability evidence section (AC: #1, #7)\n    26→  - [x] 1.1: Add `### Observability Evidence` section after existing verification requirements\n    27→  - [x] 1.2: Include instruction to query observability backend after each `docker exec` command\n    28→  - [x] 1.3: Include instruction to tag `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` when zero log events detected\n    29→  - [x] 1.4: Include instruction that observability check failure does not block verification — just logs a warning\n    30→  - [x] 1.5: Reference the VictoriaLogs query pattern from `verify-prompt.ts`\n    31→\n    32→- [x] Task 2: Verify `verify-prompt.ts` already contains observability check instructions (AC: #2)\n    33→  - [x] 2.1: Confirm `Step 3.5: Observability Check After Each Command` section exists in the prompt template\n    34→  - [x] 2.2: Confirm the VictoriaLogs query URL uses the configured endpoint\n    35→  - [x] 2.3: Confirm the `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag instruction is present\n    36→  - [x] 2.4: Write a regression test confirming the prompt output contains these sections\n    37→\n    38→- [x] Task 3: Verify `parseObservabilityGaps` in `parser.ts` handles proof content correctly (AC: #3)\n    39→  - [x] 3.1: Confirm existing `parseObservabilityGaps()` function correctly counts gaps per AC section\n    40→  - [x] 3.2: Write a test with 8 AC sections and 2 gaps, asserting `totalACs: 8, gapCount: 2, coveredCount: 6`\n    41→  - [x] 3.3: Write a test with zero gaps and one with all gaps as edge cases\n    42→\n    43→- [x] Task 4: Verify `verifyStory()` in `verify/index.ts` reports observability alongside functional results (AC: #4)\n    44→  - [x] 4.1: Confirm `verifyStory()` calls `parseObservabilityGaps()` on proof content\n    45→  - [x] 4.2: Confirm `VerifyResult.observabilityGapCount` and `runtimeCoveragePercent` are populated\n    46→  - [x] 4.3: Write a test confirming these fields appear in the returned result\n    47→\n    48→- [x] Task 5: Verify `saveRuntimeCoverage()` persists under `observability.runtime` in state (AC: #5)\n    49→  - [x] 5.1: Confirm `computeRuntimeCoverage()` and `saveRuntimeCoverage()` are called from `verifyStory()`\n    50→  - [x] 5.2: Write a test confirming `sprint-state.json` gets `observability.runtime.coveragePercent` and `lastValidationTimestamp`\n    51→  - [x] 5.3: Confirm static and runtime coverage are stored as separate objects under `observability`\n    52→\n    53→- [x] Task 6: Write unit tests for patch content validation (AC: #1)\n    54→  - [x] 6.1: Create or extend test file `src/modules/verify/__tests__/observability-patch.test.ts`\n    55→  - [x] 6.2: Test that `patches/verify/story-verification.md` contains \"### Observability Evidence\" section\n    56→  - [x] 6.3: Test that `patches/verify/story-verification.md` contains `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` instruction\n    57→  - [x] 6.4: Test that `patches/verify/story-verification.md` contains observability backend query instruction\n    58→\n    59→- [x] Task 7: Integration verification (AC: all)\n    60→  - [x] 7.1: `npm run build` — verify tsup compiles without errors\n    61→  - [x] 7.2: `npm run test:unit` — all tests pass, no regressions\n    62→  - [x] 7.3: Verify no file exceeds 300 lines (NFR9)\n    63→\n    64→## Dev Notes\n    65→\n    66→### Architecture References\n    67→\n    68→This story implements FR27 (verification includes runtime observability validation) and FR28 (patches updated with observability enforcement). It builds on:\n    69→- Epic 2 (Stories 2.1–2.3): Observability gap parsing (`parseObservabilityGaps` in `parser.ts`), runtime coverage computation (`runtime-coverage.ts`), runtime validator (`runtime-validator.ts`)\n    70→- Story 5.1: Code review observability integration (same patch update pattern)\n    71→- Architecture Decision 3: Runtime validation — verification IS the runtime check. Every `docker exec` command should produce at least one log entry.\n    72→- Architecture Decision 2: Separate metrics — static and runtime coverage reported independently.\n    73→\n    74→### Key Implementation Details\n    75→\n    76→**Most of the code already exists.** This story is primarily about:\n    77→1. Updating the verification patch (`patches/verify/story-verification.md`) to instruct the verifier to check observability\n    78→2. Confirming the verify prompt template already has the right instructions (it does — `Step 3.5`)\n    79→3. Confirming the parser and verify orchestrator already handle observability gaps (they do)\n    80→4. Writing tests that prove the end-to-end flow works\n    81→\n    82→**The verify prompt already does this.** `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` already contains `Step 3.5: Observability Check After Each Command` with the VictoriaLogs query and `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag instructions. This was implemented in Epic 2.\n    83→\n    84→**The parser already handles gaps.** `src/modules/verify/parser.ts` has `parseObservabilityGaps()` which scans proof content for `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags per AC section.\n    85→\n    86→**The orchestrator already computes coverage.** `src/modules/verify/index.ts` `verifyStory()` already calls `parseObservabilityGaps()`, sets `observabilityGapCount` and `runtimeCoveragePercent` on `VerifyResult`, and calls `computeRuntimeCoverage()` + `saveRuntimeCoverage()`.\n    87→\n    88→**What's missing is the patch.** The verification patch `patches/verify/story-verification.md` does NOT yet instruct the verifier to check observability. The prompt template does, but the patch (which is the persistent enforcement document) does not. This is the primary deliverable.\n    89→\n    90→**Graceful degradation.** If the observability backend is not running, the verifier should warn and continue. This matches the existing pattern in `runtime-validator.ts` where `checkBackendHealth()` returns false and the result is marked `skipped: true`.\n    91→\n    92→### Existing Code to Reuse\n    93→\n    94→- `patches/verify/story-verification.md` — existing verification patch to extend (primary target)\n    95→- `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` — already has observability check instructions (verify, don't rewrite)\n    96→- `src/modules/verify/parser.ts` — `parseObservabilityGaps()` already implemented\n    97→- `src/modules/verify/index.ts` — `verifyStory()` already integrates gap parsing and coverage\n    98→- `src/modules/observability/runtime-coverage.ts` — `computeRuntimeCoverage()` and `saveRuntimeCoverage()` already implemented\n    99→- `src/modules/observability/runtime-validator.ts` — `checkBackendHealth()` for graceful degradation pattern\n   100→- `src/modules/verify/types.ts` — `VerifyResult`, `ObservabilityGapResult` types already defined\n   101→\n   102→### What This Story Does NOT Include\n   103→\n   104→- No new TypeScript modules — the code infrastructure is already in place from Epic 2\n   105→- No changes to `verify-prompt.ts` — it already has the observability instructions\n   106→- No changes to `parser.ts` or `verify/index.ts` — gap parsing and coverage computation already work\n   107→- No new CLI commands — verification is triggered by the existing `codeharness verify` command\n   108→- No standalone runtime validation changes — that's Story 2.3 (already done)\n   109→\n   110→### Dependencies\n   111→\n   112→- **Depends on:** Epic 2 (observability gap parsing, runtime coverage) — DONE\n   113→- **Depends on:** Story 5.1 (code review observability, established patch update pattern) — DONE\n   114→- **Depended on by:** None — this is the last story in Epic 5 and the last story in the sprint\n   115→\n   116→### File Size Constraint\n   117→\n   118→Each new file must be under 300 lines per NFR9.\n   119→- `patches/verify/story-verification.md` — modification only, adding ~15-20 lines\n   120→- Test files — ~60-100 lines each\n   121→\n   122→### Previous Story Intelligence (Story 5.1 Code Review Observability Check)\n   123→\n   124→- Patch updates are simple markdown additions — no build or compile step needed\n   125→- Tests validate patch content by reading the file and checking for required strings (using `readFileSync`)\n   126→- The review enforcement patch (`patches/review/enforcement.md`) was extended with an `### Observability` section — same pattern applies to the verify patch\n   127→- 8 tests were created for Story 5.1 in `src/modules/review/__tests__/observability-patch.test.ts`\n   128→- Build and all 2853 tests passed with no regressions\n   129→\n   130→### Git Intelligence\n   131→\n   132→Recent commits show Story 5.1 and Epic 4 complete. Patterns:\n   133→- Patch files in `patches/` are markdown, updated by appending sections\n   134→- Tests for patch content use `readFileSync` and string matching\n   135→- Result<T> pattern with `ok()` and `fail()` from `src/types/result.ts`\n   136→- Barrel exports from `index.ts` for module boundaries\n   137→- 100% test coverage on new code\n   138→\n   139→### References\n   140→\n   141→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 3] — Runtime validation during verification\n   142→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 2] — Separate metrics\n   143→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 5.2] — Acceptance criteria\n   144→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-operational-excellence.md#FR27] — Verification includes runtime observability\n   145→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-operational-excellence.md#FR28] — Patches updated with observability enforcement\n   146→- [Source: patches/verify/story-verification.md] — Existing verification patch (target for update)\n   147→- [Source: src/templates/verify-prompt.ts] — Verify prompt template (already has observability instructions)\n   148→- [Source: src/modules/verify/parser.ts] — parseObservabilityGaps() implementation\n   149→- [Source: src/modules/verify/index.ts] — verifyStory() with observability integration\n   150→- [Source: src/modules/observability/runtime-coverage.ts] — Runtime coverage computation and persistence\n   151→\n   152→### Project Structure Notes\n   153→\n   154→- Modified files: `patches/verify/story-verification.md` (add Observability Evidence section)\n   155→- New files: `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-observability-patch.test.ts` (patch content tests + regression tests for existing observability integration)\n   156→- No module boundary changes — patches are independent artifacts read by agents at runtime\n   157→\n   158→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   159→## Verification Requirements\n   160→\n   161→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/5-2-verification-runtime-integration.proof.md`)\n   162→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   163→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100% of all new code in src/)\n   164→\n   165→## Documentation Requirements\n   166→\n   167→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (src/modules/verify/AGENTS.md if tests added there)\n   168→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/5-2-verification-runtime-integration.md`\n   169→\n   170→## Testing Requirements\n   171→\n   172→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   173→- [ ] All I/O mocked (filesystem reads for patch content)\n   174→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   175→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   176→\n   177→## Dev Agent Record\n   178→\n   179→### Agent Model Used\n   180→\n   181→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   182→\n   183→### Debug Log References\n   184→\n   185→N/A — no debug issues encountered.\n   186→\n   187→### Completion Notes List\n   188→\n   189→- Task 1: Added `### Observability Evidence` section to `patches/verify/story-verification.md` with VictoriaLogs query instruction, `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tagging, graceful degradation for unreachable backend, and reference to `verify-prompt.ts` Step 3.5.\n   190→- Tasks 2-5: Confirmed all existing code already handles observability integration — `verify-prompt.ts` has Step 3.5, `parser.ts` has `parseObservabilityGaps()`, `verify/index.ts` calls it from `verifyStory()` and populates `observabilityGapCount`/`runtimeCoveragePercent`, `runtime-coverage.ts` persists to `observability.runtime` in sprint-state.json.\n   191→- Task 6: Created `verification-observability-patch.test.ts` with 16 tests covering patch content validation (6), prompt template regression (4), parser with exact AC #3 scenario (4), VerifyResult type contract (1), runtime coverage computation contract (1).\n   192→- Task 7: Build compiles cleanly. 2871 tests pass with no regressions. All files under 300 lines.\n   193→\n   194→### Change Log\n   195→\n   196→- 2026-03-21: Story 5.2 implementation complete — patch updated, 16 tests added, all ACs satisfied.\n   197→\n   198→### File List\n   199→\n   200→- patches/verify/story-verification.md (modified — added Observability Evidence section)\n   201→- src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-observability-patch.test.ts (new — 16 tests)\n   202→- src/modules/verify/AGENTS.md (modified — added new test file entry)\n   203→- docs/exec-plans/active/5-2-verification-runtime-integration.md (new — exec plan)\n   204→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01St1ZX8VZKJ5rWiDeuqc1Kp","session_id":"63766b2b-ee05-46af-a819-a3f0370845d2","uuid":"970d6127-09ec-4ad2-8f44-6fad88a308d8","timestamp":"2026-03-21T06:36:51.556Z"}
