{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01St1ZX8VZKJ5rWiDeuqc1Kp","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review Summary**\n\nStory 5-2 code review complete. 3 MEDIUM issues found and fixed, 2 LOW items noted but not fixed. Status updated to `verifying`.\n\n**What was fixed:**\n1. **MEDIUM: VerifyResult type contract test was untyped** -- Changed plain object to `const result: VerifyResult = { ... }` so TypeScript compilation catches field removal.\n2. **MEDIUM: Missing `saveRuntimeCoverage` persistence test** -- Added test that calls `saveRuntimeCoverage()`, reads back `sprint-state.json`, and asserts `observability.runtime.coveragePercent` and `lastValidationTimestamp` exist with correct values. Also verifies static coverage is preserved separately.\n3. **MEDIUM: Patch hardcoded VictoriaLogs URL without noting configurability** -- Added note that the URL is the default and may differ based on configuration.\n\n**Coverage result:** 96.98% overall, all 121 files above 80% per-file floor. Tests: 2872 passed (112 files).\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-observability-patch.test.ts` -- 3 fixes applied\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/verify/story-verification.md` -- endpoint config note added\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-2-verification-runtime-integration.md` -- status changed to `verifying`, changelog updated\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- MEDIUM: VerifyResult type contract test used untyped object literal -- no compile-time protection against field removal (FIXED)\n- MEDIUM: AC #5 (`saveRuntimeCoverage` persistence to sprint-state.json) had no test for the actual persistence path -- task 5.2 was marked `[x]` without a test verifying file I/O (FIXED)\n- MEDIUM: Patch hardcoded VictoriaLogs URL without noting it's configurable, inconsistent with `verify-prompt.ts` which supports endpoint overrides (FIXED)\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n- LOW: Coverage percentage computation duplicated in test (line 136-139) manually replicates `(coveredCount / totalACs) * 100` instead of calling `computeRuntimeCoverage`. If formula changes, test still passes with old formula.\n- LOW: No test for `parseObservabilityGaps` when an AC section contains `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` multiple times (current code handles it correctly, but no regression test).\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None below floor. All 121 files above 80%. Overall 96.98% exceeds 90% target.\n- The `saveRuntimeCoverage` persistence path is now tested (was previously untested for this story).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The story correctly reuses existing infrastructure from Epic 2 without introducing new modules or coupling.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8e440a307fec248b (use SendMessage with to: 'a8e440a307fec248b' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 64443\ntool_uses: 49\nduration_ms: 254133</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"63766b2b-ee05-46af-a819-a3f0370845d2","uuid":"e63aa7e0-c107-4359-b514-96e34e4cbe4b","timestamp":"2026-03-21T06:40:59.592Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-2-verification-runtime-integration.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt)\n- Coverage gaps (files below floor, untested edge cases, areas needing integration tests)\n- Architecture concerns (patterns that don't fit, coupling issues, missing abstractions)\n- Items sent back for re-development (what failed and why)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"a8e440a307fec248b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review Summary**\n\nStory 5-2 code review complete. 3 MEDIUM issues found and fixed, 2 LOW items noted but not fixed. Status updated to `verifying`.\n\n**What was fixed:**\n1. **MEDIUM: VerifyResult type contract test was untyped** -- Changed plain object to `const result: VerifyResult = { ... }` so TypeScript compilation catches field removal.\n2. **MEDIUM: Missing `saveRuntimeCoverage` persistence test** -- Added test that calls `saveRuntimeCoverage()`, reads back `sprint-state.json`, and asserts `observability.runtime.coveragePercent` and `lastValidationTimestamp` exist with correct values. Also verifies static coverage is preserved separately.\n3. **MEDIUM: Patch hardcoded VictoriaLogs URL without noting configurability** -- Added note that the URL is the default and may differ based on configuration.\n\n**Coverage result:** 96.98% overall, all 121 files above 80% per-file floor. Tests: 2872 passed (112 files).\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-observability-patch.test.ts` -- 3 fixes applied\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/patches/verify/story-verification.md` -- endpoint config note added\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/5-2-verification-runtime-integration.md` -- status changed to `verifying`, changelog updated\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- MEDIUM: VerifyResult type contract test used