{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MroGLQeBqAuADM4B6HKGHs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-21\n     2→\n     3→---\n     4→\n     5→### 3-3-onboard-alias — create-story (2026-03-21T04:24Z)\n     6→\n     7→- **Previous sprint file collision:** An existing `3-3-bmad-parser-story-bridge-command.md` exists from a previous sprint's Epic 3. No conflict since new file uses `3-3-onboard-alias.md`.\n     8→- **Ambiguous AC3:** Epic says `codeharness onboard scan` should map to \"equivalent audit subcommand,\" but audit has no subcommands. Interpreted as deprecation warning + base audit run.\n     9→- **Risk: Old exports removal.** `onboard.ts` exports `getLastScanResult()`, `getLastCoverageResult()`, `getLastAuditResult()`, and `resetLastScanResult()`. Need to verify no external consumers before removing.\n    10→- **Risk: `onboard epic` subcommand has no audit equivalent.** Dropping silently may surprise users.\n    11→\n    12→### 3-3-onboard-alias — dev-story (2026-03-21T04:31Z)\n    13→\n    14→- **audit-action.ts branch coverage 95.83%:** Two uncovered branches (lines 96, 101) in JSON fix output formatting. Covered by audit.test.ts but not onboard.test.ts — redundant since both delegate to same handler.\n    15→- **Test file size:** onboard.test.ts is 325 lines vs estimated 100-150. Consistent with project norms (audit.test.ts is 407 lines).\n    16→- **console.log in shared handler:** audit-action.ts line 107 uses console.log directly. Story says \"Do NOT use console.log directly\" but formatAuditHuman() returns pre-formatted strings — wrapping in ok()/info() would double-prefix.\n    17→\n    18→### 3-3-onboard-alias — code-review (2026-03-21T04:38Z)\n    19→\n    20→- **HIGH: Unsafe double type assertion** in audit-action.ts:86 — `as unknown as Record<string, unknown>` bypassed type safety. Fixed with spread operator.\n    21→- **MEDIUM: Dead branch guard** in audit-action.ts:101 — `fixStories &&` always true at that point. Simplified to `else`.\n    22→- **MEDIUM: NFR9 violation** — onboard.test.ts at 325 lines, compacted to 230.\n    23→- **MEDIUM: Branch coverage gap** — missing test for `skipped: true` path. Added, now 100%.\n    24→- **LOW (not fixed): console.log in audit-action.ts:111** — established codebase pattern, needs new `raw()` output utility to fix properly.\n    25→- **LOW (not fixed): formatAuditJson() is pass-through no-op** — exists for symmetry only.\n    26→- **Coverage: 96.97% overall, all 119 files above 80% floor, 2783 tests pass**\n    27→\n    28→### 3-3-onboard-alias — verify (2026-03-21T05:10Z)\n    29→\n    30→- All 8 ACs passed black-box Docker verification\n    31→- Observability gaps: no structured log events emitted for any audit/onboard CLI interaction\n    32→- Pre-existing test failure in run-helpers.test.ts (--live flag test) had to be fixed before verification could proceed — not related to this story\n    33→\n    34→### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — create-story (2026-03-21T05:14Z)\n    35→\n    36→- Ambiguity: rules markdown as code vs documentation — chose hardcoded rules with markdown as reference docs\n    37→- Expanded ACs from 4 (epic) to 10 to cover each rule category individually\n    38→- Risk: regex-based validation may produce false positives for complex Dockerfiles\n    39→- `patches/infra/` directory doesn't exist yet — first file created there\n    40→\n    41→### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — dev-story (2026-03-21T05:22Z)\n    42→\n    43→- **Branch coverage at 87.5%** — The `line !== undefined` conditional in `dfGap()` helper has one branch not fully covered. Cosmetic; both paths exercised indirectly.\n    44→- **Verification tools check has potential false positives** — Regex checks for tool names anywhere in apt-get/apk lines. Matches story's stated approach: \"False positives are acceptable.\"\n    45→- **Dual file reads in checkInfrastructure** — Dockerfile read once for precondition checks, then again by `validateDockerfile()`. Intentional for backward-compatible error messages but redundant.\n    46→\n    47→### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — code-review (2026-03-21T05:32Z)\n    48→\n    49→- **HIGH: Operator precedence ambiguity** in `checkVerificationTools` — parentheses missing around `&&`/`||` chains. Fixed.\n    50→- **MEDIUM: Redundant double-read** of Dockerfile in `checkInfrastructure` — removed, delegated to `validateDockerfile`. Fixed.\n    51→- **MEDIUM: `checkNoSourceCopy` missed `COPY --chown` flag patterns** — regex updated. Fixed.\n    52→- **MEDIUM: No test for `COPY --from=` binary install pattern** — test added. Fixed.\n    53→- **LOW (not fixed): `checkVerificationTools` loose matching** — `content.includes(tool)` matches anywhere in file. Acceptable per story design.\n    54→- **LOW (not fixed): `checkBinaryOnPath` has no line number** — inconsistent with other checks but not a bug.\n    55→- **Coverage: 96.99% overall, 2817 tests, all 120 files above 80% floor**\n    56→\n    57→### 4-1-dockerfile-rules-validation — verify (2026-03-21T05:35Z)\n    58→\n    59→- 9/10 ACs passed black-box Docker verification\n    60→- **AC10 FAIL:** `validateDockerfile()` warnings stored in `DockerfileValidationResult.warnings[]` but not propagated by `checkInfrastructure()` to audit output. Fixed by adding warning-to-gap propagation in dimensions.ts. Test added (2820 tests pass). Story returned to `verifying` for re-verification in next session.\n    61→\n    62→### 4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration — create-story (2026-03-21T05:42Z)\n    63→\n    64→- Expanded from 3 epic ACs to 10 for full implementation coverage\n    65→- Risk: AC #5 (generated Dockerfile passes validateDockerfile) depends on template content matching all 6 rule categories — tight coupling with Story 4.1's validator regex\n    66→- AC #3 (generic template) — existing `templates/Dockerfile.verify` uses `COPY . /workspace/` which would fail \"no source copy\" rule. Generated templates must differ.\n    67→- Init orchestrator (`init-project.ts`) is already complex; template generation delegated to new `dockerfile-template.ts` to minimize changes\n    68→\n    69→### 4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration — dev-story (2026-03-21T05:45Z)\n    70→\n    71→- **Workaround:** Templates use single-line `apt-get install curl jq` instead of multi-line format. `validateDockerfile()` checks lines independently, so multi-line `\\` continuations cause false negatives. Templates deviate from story spec format but satisfy functional requirement (AC #5).\n    72→- **Task 5.2 skipped:** No new init-project integration tests added — init-project.ts has heavy mocking; template function fully tested via its own 22-test file.\n    73→- **Code quality concern:** `checkVerificationTools()` in dockerfile-validator.ts only checks single lines, not multi-line RUN instructions. Validator and template generator coupled to single-line format.\n    74→\n    75→### 4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration — code-review (2026-03-21T05:54Z)\n    76→\n    77→- **HIGH: Unhandled writeFileSync exception** — violates Result<T> \"never throws\" contract. Fixed with try/catch.\n    78→- **MEDIUM: Missing projectDir validation** — falsy values produce garbage paths. Fixed with guard clause.\n    79→- **MEDIUM: Test mock leak** — `vi.clearAllMocks()` doesn't reset implementations, causing pollution. Fixed with `vi.resetAllMocks()`.\n    80→- **LOW (not fixed): Redundant `resolvedStack` variable** — clear enough, no change needed.\n    81→- **Coverage gap:** init-project.test.ts does not assert on `dockerfile` field in InitResult (tests predate story 4.2).\n    82→- **Coverage: 96.98% overall, 2845 tests, all 121 files above 80% floor**\n    83→\n    84→### 4-2-dockerfile-template-dev-integration — verify (2026-03-21T06:01Z)\n    85→\n    86→- All 10 ACs passed black-box Docker verification\n    87→- No escalations, no failures\n    88→- Showboat not installed — skipping re-verification (warning only, not blocking)\n    89→\n    90→### 5-1-code-review-observability-check — create-story (2026-03-21T06:08Z)\n    91→\n    92→- **Workaround:** Sprint-status.yaml not updated by agent (per instructions) — manually reconciled after.\n    93→- **Lightweight story:** Primarily patch-file updates with minimal TypeScript code. Main work is markdown content in enforcement patches.\n    94→- **Risk:** AC #2 and #3 depend on LLM agent behavior during real review sessions — unit tests can only verify patch content exists, not agent interpretation.\n    95→- **Observation:** Epic ACs reference `patches/review/review-enforcement.md` but actual file is `patches/review/enforcement.md`.\n    96→\n    97→### 5-1-code-review-observability-check — dev-story (2026-03-21T06:12Z)\n    98→\n    99→No issues reported. Clean implementation — 8 new tests, 2853 total pass, zero regressions.\n   100→\n   101→### 5-1-code-review-observability-check — code-review (2026-03-21T06:16Z)\n   102→\n   103→- **MEDIUM (fixed): Review patch missing `--json` flag** in Semgrep command — would produce wrong output format.\n   104→- **MEDIUM (fixed): Tautological test** — Semgrep JSON contract test validated hardcoded mock against itself. Replaced with real `parseSemgrepOutput()` integration.\n   105→- **MEDIUM (fixed): Module-scope `readFileSync`** — test file crashes entirely if patch file missing. Moved to `beforeAll`.\n   106→- **LOW (not fixed): Em dash vs double dash inconsistency** between patch and analyzer.ts — pre-existing tech debt.\n   107→- **LOW (not fixed): Fragile `ROOT` path resolution** using `__dirname` + four `..` segments.\n   108→- **Coverage: 96.98% overall, 2855 tests, all 121 files above 80% floor**\n   109→\n   110→### 5-1-code-review-observability-check — verify (2026-03-21T06:22Z)\n   111→\n   112→- **Infrastructure issue (fixed):** verify-env prepare does NOT copy patches/ into the Docker container. Container uses globally installed npm package (v0.23.1) which predates this story's changes. First verification run failed 5/6 ACs because patches were stale.\n   113→- **Fix applied:** Manually copied updated patches into container via `docker cp`. Re-verification passed 6/6.\n   114→- **Systemic concern:** Any story that modifies `patches/` will hit this same issue. The verify-env prepare or Docker image needs to include current patches, not just the published npm version.\n   115→- **ACs #2-#4 verified via patch content + semgrep tooling** rather than live Claude agent sessions (Claude CLI wasn't authenticated in container). This is a reasonable proxy but not a full integration test.\n   116→\n   117→### 5-2-verification-runtime-integration — create-story (2026-03-21T06:30Z)\n   118→\n   119→- **Ambiguity in epic definition:** Epic AC #2 says \"verify-prompt.ts is updated\" but the template already contains observability instructions from Epic 2. Interpreted as confirmation/regression-test task.\n   120→- **Workaround:** Sprint-status.yaml not modified by subagent (per instructions) — updated by harness-run after.\n   121→- **Risk — thin story:** Most code already exists from Epic 2. Story is largely patch update + test writing. Risk of dev agent over-engineering.\n   122→- **Observation:** Last story in Epic 5 and last story in the sprint. No downstream dependencies.\n   123→\n   124→### 5-2-verification-runtime-integration — dev-story (2026-03-21T06:37Z)\n   125→\n   126→None. Clean implementation — 16 new tests, 2871 total pass, zero regressions.\n   127→\n   128→### 5-2-verification-runtime-integration — code-review (2026-03-21T06:45Z)\n   129→\n   130→- **MEDIUM (fixed): VerifyResult type contract test was untyped** — no compile-time protection against field removal. Fixed with explicit type annotation.\n   131→- **MEDIUM (fixed): Missing `saveRuntimeCoverage` persistence test** — AC #5 had no test for actual file I/O persistence path. Added.\n   132→- **MEDIUM (fixed): Patch hardcoded VictoriaLogs URL** without noting configurability, inconsistent with verify-prompt.ts endpoint overrides. Fixed.\n   133→- **LOW (not fixed): Coverage percentage computation duplicated in test** — manually replicates formula instead of calling computeRuntimeCoverage.\n   134→- **LOW (not fixed): No test for parseObservabilityGaps with multiple gaps in one AC section.**\n   135→- **Coverage: 96.98% overall, 2872 tests, all 121 files above 80% floor**\n   136→\n   137→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01DGSVg5vuF7NmXt4St6ubJQ","session_id":"63766b2b-ee05-46af-a819-a3f0370845d2","uuid":"f7ac02f6-6e07-40ce-8186-cd4196928ec5","timestamp":"2026-03-21T06:41:51.282Z"}
